Resonance of a Ghost

Challenge Description
It was 03:14 AM when the monitoring station in CC-3 flagged a 60-second spike coming from Node B4—a terminal that hasn't been officially powered on since the campus network upgrade.

The security team labeled the capture as "The Resonance." On the surface, it’s nothing but a pocket of high-entropy digital corruption—chaotic, rhythmic, and seemingly meaningless. Every automated forensic suite we've thrown at it has returned a total null result. It’s as if the data is purposely hiding in the static, mocking our standard reconstruction protocols.

Our lead investigator left a single, cryptic note on the terminal before walking off the project:

"There is a ghost in the noise, and it refuses to speak. It’s not just hidden; it’s choosing to be invisible."

The file is all that remains. Make it speak.

